reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Easy to assemble, sturdy, cute, compact size for any space.My only complaint is that, though the lights come with their own controllers, they don't work independently. So if he wants blue and I want pink, they're both the same color, if I want my light off his has to be off.The seller also includes a bag of extra pieces! So, if you lose a screw while assembling you can grab the extra.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars I like the set but one of the lights changes setting randomly.
reviews.reviewText: I like the set. They do the job, look nice, and are reasonably sturdy. They drawers are a little flimsy, so you can't put anything too heavy in them. But really your .45 should be in a lock box, and it's mostly random stuff that ends up in the drawers anyway. There was enough room on the open shelf above the drawers for a CPAP machine, and enough room on the top for a clock and whatever tech you want to charge. The wireless charger worked pretty well with my Galaxy phone, but sometimes it's a little tricky to find the sweet spot to get the charging going.The only complaint I have about the set is that the light strip on one of the stands changes settings randomly on its own. I like to have the red light on most of the time, because its not too bright and doesn't mess with you night vision, but you can still see the floor around the bed. But sometimes it will go into demo mode and I will wake up in the middle of the night with it flashing and changing colors. The light in the other stand works fine, so I guess I just drew the short straw and got a wonky one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Very easy to build, very sturdy/ solid. I have put together a lot of package furniture and this was the best experience I have had. They don’t wobble, very stable and they look great!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wonderful bedside table
reviews.reviewText: I love this table! It was very easy to put together. There is so much storage and the outlets and wireless phone charger are great. The led light makes for a nice light before going to sleep. The only thing I don't like is that is is a little short. The top is the same height as my mattress. I would be better (for me) if it was 7 inches taller, then the second shelf would be easier accessible. But I am very happy with my purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These are pretty good little nightstands. They are smaller than I expected, but they still have quite a bit of storage space for their size, and that is what I wanted. Only reason I’m giving them 3 stars is because the lights on them turn on all on their own and they will do the super fast flashing, like a strobe light out of nowhere. They each have their own remote, but the one remote will control both. So when you try to turn one skitso light off, the other will turn on. Other than that, they are decent little nightstands.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Very easy to assemble. Almost don’t need instructions. The duo set works great for a small bedroom and the lights give it a nice pop

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble
reviews.reviewText: This product may not be fine furniture but it's not cheap looking. Better quality than similar items in its price point. Each nightstand has more room than any others I have owned and the LEDs and charging station are a nice perk and function well. Arrived in a compact package with limited packaging (envirofriendly) and only took about 15 minutes to assemble. Directions were pretty clear and easy to follow.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute but small
reviews.reviewText: These are cute but definitely look too small next to a cal king bed. These are perfect next to either a twin, full, or Maybe a queen size bed. Wouldn't recommend to buy if u have anything bigger than a queen. Hope this helps.

After building these two nightstands I plugged them in only to find one of the electrical units does not work. Really unfortunate because this was the draw for us purchasing these stands. The seller is impossible to contact and Amazon can only assist me if I am willing to ship the two night stands back after I spent two hours building them. I’d rather not.Perhaps the seller will see this and offer a better solution. Until then, buyer beware that quality control on the electrical might not be the best.Update : I was refunded the import fees. I guess that’s something
